<dl id="n41132a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41132a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41132a"> 132(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> described by / parishioners as / one of the best of / good fellows</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[Exhibit 15a: Extract from <i>Daily Sketch</i>, 9 February, contd.]</font>: The three principal figures in the <font color="green">[hyoscine]</font> case are&mdash; The Rev. Horace George Bolding (39), curate of Lingfield (Surrey) Parish Church, found dead on his bed in his dressing-gown on January 4. <mark>Described by parishioners as &ldquo;Happy, jovial, one of the best of good fellows</mark>, and a regular sport.&rdquo; <small> Filson Young, <a name="FYTF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FYTF"><cite title="source">Trial of Frederick Bywaters and Edith Thompson</cite></a> (1923) 171</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
